<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcf77825d-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s1425e"><num value="1425e">§ 1425e.</num><heading> Additional powers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Powers granted herein shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any powers granted by other law to, or for the benefit or assistance of, any public corporate authority.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcf77825e-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/171/s5">Pub. L. 88–171, § 5</ref>, <date date="1963-11-04">Nov. 4, 1963</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/77/304">77 Stat. 304</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcf77825f-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idcf778260-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idcf778261-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Organic Act of Guam which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
